[2] South Africa
Date: Wed 7 Apr 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: SABCnews [edited]
<http://www.sabcnews.com/south_africa/health/0,2172,77433,00.html>

8 new cholera cases in North West
---------------------------------
8 new cases of cholera have been reported during the last 24 hours in the
Kanana township near Klerksdorp, the North West health department said on
Wed 7 Apr 2004.
Baba Gaoganediwe, the departmental spokesperson, said in a statement that
58 people were still being treated in hospital for cholera. Since the
outbreak of the disease last week, 78 cases had been reported. 2 people
have died of the disease.
Gaoganediwe says that, due to a collective effort by the provincial and
national health departments, the department of water affairs and forestry,
the Klerksdorp municipality, the water board, and local doctors, the
outbreak has been brought under control.
The source of the disease remained a mystery, especially after water
samples tested negative for cholera.
Gaoganediwe says investigations into the source of the disease are
continuing. "The focus of the department and of our outbreak response team
is on management of patients, health promotion, public awareness, attention
to sanitation and surveillance," he said. "We remain confident that through
our hard work and attention to every lead, the source of this outbreak will
be found."
